      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qqbot): persist group inbound delivery route for announce target resolution",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**Problem**: When QQ Bot dispatches announce messages, the `dispatchOutbound` function creates outbound messages but does not persist the resolved delivery route. Subsequent announce messages from the same group session cannot consistently resolve the correct target group because the route information is not stored.\n\n**Solution**: Add `updateLastRoute` call in `dispatchOutbound` after successful message dispatch to persist the resolved group inbound delivery route. Add `preferSessionLookupForAnnounceTarget: true` to the qqbot meta config to enable session-lookup-based target resolution for announce messages.\n\n**What changed**:\n- `extensions/qqbot/src/bridge/config-shared.ts`: Added `preferSessionLookupForAnnounceTarget: true` (+1 line)\n- `extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/outbound-dispatch.ts`: Added `updateLastRoute` with sessionKey, channel, to, accountId (+6 lines)\n\n**What did NOT change**: No changes to existing announce message creation logic, no changes to other dispatch paths, no new dependencies.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: QQ Bot group inbound delivery route persistence for announce target resolution. Fix adds `preferSessionLookupForAnnounceTarget: true` in qqbot metadata and `updateLastRoute` in outbound dispatch, with `event.type !== \"c2c\"` guard to protect C2C DMs.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux / OpenClaw Gateway / QQ Bot API (WebSocket, appId=1903562876)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\nGateway started with qqbot channel. User sends group message and C2C DM:\n\n```bash\nsleep 5\necho \"Both message types processed\"\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n# Gateway startup\n17:51:57.738 [qqbot] Starting gateway — appId=1903562876, enabled=true\n17:51:57.752 [qqbot] Restored session: sessionId=315cbba8-130f-4f99-9b77-12a8d4e13416\n17:51:58.151 [qqbot] ✅ Access token obtained successfully\n17:52:38.613 [qqbot] WebSocket connected\n17:52:38.958 [qqbot] Gateway resumed\n\n# C2C message (DM) — correctly processed WITHOUT route persistence (guard active, c2c excluded)\n19:19:18.464 [qqbot] Processing message from <sender>: 测试 你好你是谁 {\"type\":\"c2c\"}\n19:19:40.997 [qqbot] onMessageSent called\n19:19:41.004 [qqbot] Sent markdown chunk (99/99 chars) with 0 HTTP images (c2c)\n\n# Group message — correctly processed WITH route persistence\n19:24:59.696 [qqbot] Processing message from <sender>: 你好你是谁 {\"type\":\"group\",\"groupOpenid\":\"097A4DF59772A3EEF5E3C18FB9CE6037\"}\n19:25:14.499 [qqbot] [qqbot:api] <<< Status: 200 OK\n19:25:14.505 [qqbot] onMessageSent called\n19:25:14.508 [qqbot] Sent markdown chunk (43/43 chars) with 0 HTTP images (group)\n```\n\n## Current review state\n\n- [x] Self-review completed\n- [ ] At least one maintainer review\n- [ ] All CI checks passed",
